<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="419" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3892/2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Snyder</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Jamaica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-16"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Fearful earthquake followed by fire; Kingston destroyed; hundreds of
                            lives lost; food sadly wanted. Consulate partially destroyed; fireproof
                            safe.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consul.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>